<br>
From a RP stance it makes as much sense as not being able to harm other player-characters on a blue server.  I can cast nukes at another PC all day long and if we aren't dueling, guildwarring, on a zek, or in an arena (/wave Gem) I can't hurt them.  This means if I have my dragon-allied toon training on raids into NToV even if I wanted to.  It would be impossible, the NPCs would be immune to my attacks and would laugh-off any means I would have to anger them.<br>
<br>
The only exploit I can think of would be surrounding having your healers on the faction of the forces you're attacking, and using the &quot;no-aggro&quot; rule to avoid having them get eaten or even having to worry about camping them out in a raid wipe.  The solution I contemplate is akin to the &quot;blues can't affect reds&quot; rule and that is once someone aggroes your faction, you are unable to affect them with beneficial spells, although the coding for *that* would be nightmarish I have a feeling.  Even without that, its no worse than having cross-team healers in a PvP teams server be immune to the other side's attacks. <p>--------------<br>
