 anyone, and can freely attack and aggro members of that faction (for faction switching) if you wanted to.<br>
<br>
Honestly I like the idea of a toggleable PvP switch.  If I want to play PvP I can go to the PoD and be made PvP+ and when I wanted to return to PvP- I could find the Priest of Order (PoO?) and do so.  That way, if I just wanted to xp and not worry about it, or I wanted to participate in a raid as my cleric, I could switch it back to PvP- and play and have fun.  If I find my corpse being camped by a griefer PK, I could go turn my PvP flag off, give him a gigantic /rude, and then go about looting my corpse.<br>
<br>
Either way, I wish Gem would get the point about this thread.  We know what the current methods are, we are talking about what OTHER methods of being PvP+ on a normal &quot;blue&quot; server might be fun/workable without worrying about it being permanent or screwing up our game play. <p>--------------<br>
